Unemployment Analysis using Python

Problem Understanding:

Unemployment rate represents the percentage of unemployed people in the total labour force. During the Covid-19 pandemic, India witnessed a sharp rise in unemployment due to lockdowns, business shutdowns, and reduced economic activity. This project aims to analyze unemployment trends across regions and time, especially before and during Covid-19.

In [18]:
covid_df = df1[df1['Date'] >= '2020-03-01']

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
sns.lineplot(data=covid_df, x='Date', y='Estimated_Unemployment_Rate_(%)', hue='Region')
plt.title("Unemployment Rate During Covid-19")
plt.legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1))
plt.show()

In [20]:
region_avg = df2.groupby('Region')['Estimated_Unemployment_Rate_(%)'].mean().sort_values()

plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))
region_avg.plot(kind='barh')
plt.title("Average Unemployment Rate by Region")
plt.xlabel("Unemployment Rate (%)")
plt.show()

Key Findings:

1] Unemployment rate increased sharply during Covid-19 (MarchMay 2020)

2] Urban regions were more impacted than rural regions

3] Certain states showed extreme spikes due to economic dependency on services

4] Post-lockdown recovery is visible in later months

5] Regional disparity in employment patterns exists across India

Conclusion

This analysis highlights the severe impact of Covid-19 on employment in India. Data visualization and exploratory analysis helped identify trends, regional disparities, and recovery patterns. Such insights can assist policymakers in designing targeted employment and economic recovery programs.
